1) ps aux -> it will shows the process running in your system
options
-f ->display full information
-e ->shows all process
-u -> username
example
ps aux | grep chrome
it will display all the process running in chrome

2)  monitor the system 
top -> monitor the system activity
it will dispaly all real time dyanamic views of your system
this command also shows the cpu utlization, memory utilization and pid so on


3) kill command or terminating  forcefully
 force stop your process
ex:-> kill pid( here pid means process id)
kill 1201


4) process state 
running, sleeping , stoped, zombie
1) running -> currently executing 
2) sleeping -> waiting for an event fo proced
3) stopped -> stoped by the user or  signal
4) zombie -> terminated but not yet cleaned up 
